      p Mathematics has always been a great pastime for me.
      p I have invented quite a few visualisations and generators for several interesting pieces of mathematics, some of which you can see and try on my&nbsp;
        +external-link('https://github.com/danwdart/projects/tree/master/js/maths') projects repo on GitHub
      p Some notable (read: working right now) examples are:
      ul
        li
          +external-link('https://rawgit.com/danwdart/projects/master/js/maths/src/cfe/index.html') Continued Fraction Expander
        li A set of gravity simulators 
          +external-link('https://rawgit.com/danwdart/gravity/master/2/gravity.html') (sun version, left click for planets, middle click for stars)
          |, 
          +external-link('https://rawgit.com/danwdart/gravity/master/4/gravity.html') (black hole version)
        li
          +external-link('https://rawgit.com/danwdart/projects/master/js/maths/src/cellautomata/index.html') Cell Automata
        li
          +external-link('https://rawgit.com/danwdart/projects/master/js/maths/src/sternbrocot/sbgraphtones.html') Stern-Brocot Graph Tones (warning: loud audio)
          br
          | &nbsp;(this is actually the answer similar to 
          +external-link('https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zSL8asTgpzA') the riddle 
          | I posed on my YouTube channel)
        li
          +external-link('https://rawgit.com/danwdart/projects/master/js/rolling/index.html') Rolling Shutter effect example
      p My current&nbsp;
        a(href='https://oeis.org',target='_blank',title='Online Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences') OEIS
        | &nbsp;contributions are:
      ul
        li
          +external-link('https://oeis.org/A275124') A275124: Multiples of 5 where Pisano periods of Fibonacci numbers A001175 and Lucas numbers A106291 agree.
        li
          a(href='https://oeis.org/A275167',target='_blank' ) A275167: Pisano periods of A275124.